the diversity of hierarchy, family, creation, order, are expressed as a divine overcoming of the material order that cannot help but come from nothingness, & in some eschatologies, must return to nothingness
the gods multiply as further differentiations from the primordial waters which are the only ultimate unity that can exist in the order of imagination & sensation
the elements, the sky, the land, etc. are all principles that emerge as actual in direct contrast to the chaotic mere possibility of being

& so polytheism makes sense on this reading, where the first contrast with the waters of chaos, the undifferentiated unity of possibility barely above non being, is the *diversity of order*. the many emerging from the one.
so to see the origin as the undifferentiated waters of chaos is to see existence as necessarily material & to search for a bottom materiality (modern pop science does this with quantum physics)

christianity sees the one over the many as an order of transcendence, where the origin is not the least determinate but the *most* determinate. it's a philosophical insight where the formal is per se prior to the material, perfect prior to the imperfect.
the disanalogy here is in the materialism, not the priority of one over the many, which both polytheism & monotheism may share

this isn't even entirely wrong from a monotheistic view. dionysius' via negativa establishes a relationship between god & nothing (it's that god exceeds our understanding so much that all our concepts, even being, fail to capture him. he can therefore be seen as nothing to us).

this indeterminacy is the chaos, the primordial water, the ground of possibility that is closer to non being than being. the original material unity, then, is this undefined, undifferentiated source of possibility.
in material terms, what is potential is prior to what is actual, what is indeterminate is prior to what is determinate, what can be is prior to what is
think of unity before multiplicity, uniformity before diversity, one before the many, but subordinate these concepts to sense & imagination
